cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication challenges in IoT devices, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes the integration of unmanned ground vehicles (UGVs) for backscatter data collection, which falls under the scope of robotics. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses power allocation and optimization challenges in backscatter communication, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a joint mobility and communication model for UGVs, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with energy minimization and optimization challenges in UGV backscatter systems, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
